'''Borneo''' ({{lang-ms|Borneo}}, {{lang-id|Kalimantan}}) is the [[List of islands by area|third largest island in the world]] and is located north of Australia, at the geographic centre of [[Maritime Southeast Asia]].

The island is divided among three countries: [[Brunei]], [[Indonesia]] and [[Malaysia]]. Approximately 73% of the island is Indonesian territory. The Malaysian states of [[Sabah]] and [[Sarawak]] in the north occupy about 26% of the island. The sovereign state of [[Brunei]], located on the north coast, comprises about 1% of Borneo's land area. It has the oldest rainforest in the world ahead of the [[Amazon rainforest]] in [[Brazil]].{{cn|date=May 2011}}

==Geography==
[[Image:Mount kinabalu 01.png|thumb|left|[[Mount Kinabalu]]]]
{{nowrap|Borneo is surrounded}} by the [[South China Sea]] to the north and northwest, the [[Sulu Sea]] to the northeast, the [[Celebes Sea]] and the [[Makassar Strait]] to the east, and the [[Java Sea]] and [[Karimata Strait]] to the south. It is the largest island in the [[Malay archipelago]], with an area of {{convert|743330|km2|sqmi}}. To the west of Borneo are the [[Malay Peninsula]] and [[Sumatra]]. To the south is [[Java (island)|Java]]. To the east is [[Sulawesi]], and to the northeast, the [[Philippines]].

Borneo's highest point is [[Mount Kinabalu]] in [[Sabah]], [[Malaysia]], with an elevation of {{convert|4095|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} above [[sea level]] it is the third highest peak in [[South East Asia]], making Borneo the world's [[List of islands by highest point|third highest island]].

The largest river system is the [[Kapuas River|Kapuas]] in [[West Kalimantan]]. With a length of {{convert|1143|km|abbr=on}}, it is the longest river in Indonesia. Malaysia's longest river, the [[Rajang River|Rajang]], lies in Sarawak and is {{convert|562.5|km|abbr=on}} long. Other major rivers include the [[Barito River|Barito]] in [[South Kalimantan]] ({{convert|880|km|mi|abbr=on|adj=mid|long}}) and the [[Mahakam River|Mahakam]] in [[East Kalimantan]] ({{convert|980|km|mi|abbr=on|adj=mid|long}}).

Borneo has significant cave systems. Clearwater Cave, for example, has one of the world's longest underground rivers. [[Deer Cave]] is home to over three million [[bat]]s, with [[guano]] accumulated to over {{convert|100|m}} high.&lt;ref&gt;BBC-TV: Planet Earth&lt;/ref&gt;

